-- UniCredit buys back senior bonds for 2.53 bln euros
-- By Valentina Za
-- Fri Jun 13, 2014 01:44AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, June 13 (Reuters) - UniCredit <CRDI.MI> has repurchased senior bonds maturing in 2016 and 2017 for an overall nominal value of 2.533 billion euros ($3.4 bln) in a successful buyback aimed at cutting excess debt and easing the redemption burden in those years.

